three weeks following an agreement with the local authorities which control
the state health service. The settlement was based on a two-year pay deal
giving the doctors a 3 per cent pay rise, but subtracting two days of
holiday. Another parallel dispute over the introduction of a new system for
administering family doctors has been sidelined by a row in parliament which
may halt the reform.
