<HEADLINE>
FT  29 MAR 94 / World News in Brief: Playwright Eugene Ionesco dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Romanian-born French playwright Eugene Ionesco (left), one of a group of
'absurdist' writers whose work dominated postwar European theatre, died in
Paris aged 81. Ionesco captivated audiences worldwide with a unique blend of
black humour and farce. His most famous plays, La Lecon, Les Chaises, La
Cantatrice Chauve and Rhinoceros were written in the 1950s. A militant
anti-Communist, Ionesco campaigned from exile against former Romanian
dictator Nicolae Ceaucescu.
