<HEADLINE>
FT  28 MAR 94 / World News in Brief: Eurofighter makes maiden flight after
two-year delay
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Eurofighter 2000 combat aircraft made a 40-minute maiden flight
yesterday at Manching in Germany. Eurofighter, being developed by a
consortium comprising British Aerospace in the UK, Alenia in Italy, Casa in
Spain and Dasa in Germany, is two years behind schedule after a series of
technical and political problems. Production is expected to begin in 1996 or
1997 and delivery to the RAF, which wants 250 aircraft, from 2000.
Development and production costs are expected to reach Pounds 32bn, with
Britain's share likely to be Pounds 12bn.
