FT  28 MAR 94 / Italy goes to polls under new system
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Achille Occhetto, leader of the seven-party Progressive Alliance, signals
his hopes for victory in the Italian general election which began yesterday.
Italy's 48m voters have started two days of polling in what is seen as the
country's most unpredictable general election since democracy was restored
after the second world war. The election marks the formal end of the postwar
dominance of Italian politics by the Christian Democrats and their allies.
Report, Page 14
