<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices were again firmer because of the limited availability,
reports Man Producten. The harvest is almost over in India and Brazil and
Indonesia have not been eager sellers. White pepper prices also remained
steady, although demand for nearby positions was slow. Buying interest for
new crop positions was picking up in Europe, however. Muntok/Sarawak faq was
quoted at USDollars 2,900 a tonne for spot supplies, with March-April
shipment at Dollars 2,875 and July-August at Dollars 2,700. Nutmeg prices
were firmer on the local market in Indonesia, where carryover stocks are
smaller than usual and estimates of the new production low. Grenada
certainly will not spoil the market, so there is room for firmer prices
again. Cassia was still weak, as were pimentos and cloves.
</TEXT>
