<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 94 / Lawrence wins cabinet seat
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ms Carmen Lawrence, the former West Australian premier and a newcomer to
Canberra politics, was yesterday given the health and human services
portfolio and a seat in cabinet in the fourth reshuffle undertaken by Mr
Paul Keating, Australia's prime minister, in as many months, writes Nikki
Tait in Sydney.
The decision to combine human services with the health job means that Mr
Brian Howe, the deputy prime minister, loses these responsibilities but
becomes minister for housing and regional development - picking up the
regional job from industry minister Peter Cook.
Mr Cook, in turn, takes on responsibilities for science. Mr John Faulkner
becomes minister for the environment, sport and territories.
